    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "How about using proper integer types in place of old int/long/unsigned/etc? I mean C99 `bool` from `stdbool.h` for boolean values, `uint_leastN_t` from `stdint.h` for bitflags, `size_t` for array indexes and so on? I am currently using this approach for my code (except for `int` in place of `bool`): it is easy to change from `bool`/`uint_*`/`size_t` to old types, but hard to replace `int`/`long`/`unsigned` with `bool`/â€¦.\n",
